works out smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Updated the test to avoid using `Mockito.when()` / `verify()` on the directly-created inline construction mock.\n\nThe failure happened because the test creates an `InlineByteBuddyMockMaker` instance directly, so `Mockito.when(mock...)` looked up mocks through Mockito’s global/default mock maker registry and did not recognize the constructed object as a mock.\n\nChanged:\n\n`tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/InlineDelegateByteBuddyMockMakerInnerInlineConstructionMockContextTest.java`\n\nNow the initializer only captures and asserts the construction context:\n\n- calls `context.constructor()` to cover the target dynamic-access sites\n- captures `context.arguments()`\n- asserts the constructed object is recorded by `control.getMocks()`\n- avoids stubbing/verifying through global Mockito APIs\n\nNo metadata files were modified.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ec753bfee22910d016a2ace2157e481909a9e1baabfc0d39e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 962, "output": 450, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45444, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781190165904, "responseId": "resp_0ec753bfee22910d016a2ace16e21c819088349dc6a83230c8"}}
